Step1: Install Node using nvm follow step from here https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-node-js-on-ubuntu-16-04 or follow these steps:
1.Use these commands:
sudo apt-get update 
sudo apt-get install build-essential libssl-dev
curl -sL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/creationix/nvm/v0.31.0/install.sh -o install_nvm.sh
bash install_nvm.sh

2.Then close and relaunch terminal and use this command
nvm ls-remote

3.Then a list of version will show up use that to download the lates version
nvm install X.X.X

4.Check for node version with node -v

Step2: import the package.json and Gruntfile.js file from git

step3: then use npm install to install all packages

step4: add icons to icon folder make sure format is svg

step5: open directory in terminal and use command grunt



